        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Extended Description</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Tachometer Output Signal</emph>
            </para>
            <para>The following discussion is only for auxiliary tachometers installed by the body builder or vehicle
                owner. It does not apply to the instrument cluster tachometer which is operated from the ATA data line.
            </para>
            <para>The ECM receives a signal from the CMP sensor and calculates engine speed (rpm). The ECM sends the
                calculated engine speed as a digital buffered TACH signal from the ECM connector to the owner installed
                tachometer.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Notes</emph>
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
